module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Filter

-- | A filter used to limit results when describing inbound or outbound
--   cross-cluster search connections. Multiple values can be specified per
--   filter. A cross-cluster search connection must match at least one of
--   the specified values for it to be returned from an operation.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newFilter</a> smart constructor.
data Filter
Filter' :: Maybe (NonEmpty Text) -> Maybe Text -> Filter

-- | Contains one or more values for the filter.
[$sel:values:Filter'] :: Filter -> Maybe (NonEmpty Text)

-- | Specifies the name of the filter.
[$sel:name:Filter'] :: Filter -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Filter</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:values:Filter'</a>, <a>filter_values</a> - Contains one or
--   more values for the filter.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Filter'</a>, <a>filter_name</a> - Specifies the name of
--   the filter.
newFilter :: Filter

-- | Contains one or more values for the filter.
filter_values :: Lens' Filter (Maybe (NonEmpty Text))

-- | Specifies the name of the filter.
filter_name :: Lens' Filter (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Filter.Filter

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus

-- | Specifies the coonection status of an inbound cross-cluster search
--   connection.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newInboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus</a> smart
--   constructor.
data InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus
InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode -> InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus

-- | Specifies verbose information for the inbound connection status.
[$sel:message:InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus'] :: InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The state code for inbound connection. This can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by
--   destination domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by destination
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and cannot be used
--   further.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:statusCode:InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus'] :: InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus -> Maybe InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode

-- | Create a value of <a>InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus</a>
--   with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>inboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus_message</a> - Specifies
--   verbose information for the inbound connection status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCode:InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>inboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus_statusCode</a> - The
--   state code for inbound connection. This can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by
--   destination domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by destination
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and cannot be used
--   further.</li>
--   </ul>
newInboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus :: InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus

-- | Specifies verbose information for the inbound connection status.
inboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus_message :: Lens' InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The state code for inbound connection. This can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by
--   destination domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by destination
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and cannot be used
--   further.</li>
--   </ul>
inboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus_statusCode :: Lens' InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus (Maybe InboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode)

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType

-- | Type of Log File, it can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>INDEX_SLOW_LOGS: Index slow logs contain insert requests that took
--   more time than configured index query log threshold to execute.</li>
--   <li>SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS: Search slow logs contain search queries that
--   took more time than configured search query log threshold to
--   execute.</li>
--   <li>ES_APPLICATION_LOGS: Elasticsearch application logs contain
--   information about errors and warnings raised during the operation of
--   the service and can be useful for troubleshooting.</li>
--   <li>AUDIT_LOGS: Audit logs contain records of user requests for access
--   from the domain.</li>
--   </ul>
newtype LogType
LogType' :: Text -> LogType
[fromLogType] :: LogType -> Text
pattern LogType_AUDIT_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_ES_APPLICATION_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_INDEX_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSONKey Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSONKey Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Headers.ToHeader Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Log.ToLog Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.ByteString.ToByteString Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Text.ToText Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Text.FromText Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.LogType.LogType

--   internal database.

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState

-- | The state of a requested change. One of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Processing: The request change is still in-process.</li>
--   <li>Active: The request change is processed and deployed to the
--   Elasticsearch domain.</li>
--   </ul>
newtype OptionState
OptionState' :: Text -> OptionState
[fromOptionState] :: OptionState -> Text
pattern OptionState_Active :: OptionState
pattern OptionState_Processing :: OptionState
pattern OptionState_RequiresIndexDocuments :: OptionState
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSONKey Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSONKey Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Network.AWS.Data.Headers.ToHeader Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Network.AWS.Data.Log.ToLog Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Network.AWS.Data.ByteString.ToByteString Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Network.AWS.Data.Text.ToText Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Network.AWS.Data.Text.FromText Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance GHC.Classes.Ord Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionState.OptionState

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionStatus

-- | Provides the current status of the entity.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOptionStatus</a> smart constructor.
data OptionStatus
OptionStatus' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Natural -> POSIX -> POSIX -> OptionState -> OptionStatus

-- | Indicates whether the Elasticsearch domain is being deleted.
[$sel:pendingDeletion:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the latest version for the entity.
[$sel:updateVersion:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> Maybe Natural

-- | Timestamp which tells the creation date for the entity.
[$sel:creationDate:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> POSIX

-- | Timestamp which tells the last updated time for the entity.
[$sel:updateDate:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> POSIX

-- | Provides the <tt>OptionState</tt> for the Elasticsearch domain.
[$sel:state:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> OptionState

-- | Create a value of <a>OptionStatus</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:pendingDeletion:OptionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>optionStatus_pendingDeletion</a> - Indicates whether the
--   Elasticsearch domain is being deleted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateVersion:OptionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>optionStatus_updateVersion</a> - Specifies the latest version for
--   the entity.
--   
--   <a>$sel:creationDate:OptionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>optionStatus_creationDate</a> - Timestamp which tells the creation
--   date for the entity.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateDate:OptionStatus'</a>, <a>optionStatus_updateDate</a> -
--   Timestamp which tells the last updated time for the entity.
--   
--   <a>$sel:state:OptionStatus'</a>, <a>optionStatus_state</a> - Provides
--   the <tt>OptionState</tt> for the Elasticsearch domain.
newOptionStatus :: UTCTime -> UTCTime -> OptionState -> OptionStatus

-- | Indicates whether the Elasticsearch domain is being deleted.
optionStatus_pendingDeletion :: Lens' OptionStatus (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the latest version for the entity.
optionStatus_updateVersion :: Lens' OptionStatus (Maybe Natural)

-- | Timestamp which tells the creation date for the entity.
optionStatus_creationDate :: Lens' OptionStatus UTCTime

-- | Timestamp which tells the last updated time for the entity.
optionStatus_updateDate :: Lens' OptionStatus UTCTime

-- | Provides the <tt>OptionState</tt> for the Elasticsearch domain.
optionStatus_state :: Lens' OptionStatus OptionState
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.AdvancedOptionsStatus

-- | Status of the advanced options for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
--   Currently, the following advanced options are available:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Option to allow references to indices in an HTTP request body.
--   Must be <tt>false</tt> when configuring access to individual
--   sub-resources. By default, the value is <tt>true</tt>. See
--   <a>Configuration Advanced Options</a> for more information.</li>
--   <li>Option to specify the percentage of heap space that is allocated
--   to field data. By default, this setting is unbounded.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Configuring Advanced Options</a>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAdvancedOptionsStatus</a> smart constructor.
data AdvancedOptionsStatus
AdvancedOptionsStatus' :: HashMap Text Text -> OptionStatus -> AdvancedOptionsStatus

-- | Specifies the status of advanced options for the specified
--   Elasticsearch domain.
[$sel:options:AdvancedOptionsStatus'] :: AdvancedOptionsStatus -> HashMap Text Text

-- | Specifies the status of <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for advanced options for
--   the specified Elasticsearch domain.
[$sel:status:AdvancedOptionsStatus'] :: AdvancedOptionsStatus -> OptionStatus

-- | Create a value of <a>AdvancedOptionsStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:options:AdvancedOptionsStatus'</a>,
--   <a>advancedOptionsStatus_options</a> - Specifies the status of
--   advanced options for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:AdvancedOptionsStatus'</a>,
--   <a>advancedOptionsStatus_status</a> - Specifies the status of
--   <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for advanced options for the specified
--   Elasticsearch domain.
newAdvancedOptionsStatus :: OptionStatus -> AdvancedOptionsStatus

-- | Specifies the status of advanced options for the specified
--   Elasticsearch domain.
advancedOptionsStatus_options :: Lens' AdvancedOptionsStatus (HashMap Text Text)

-- | Specifies the status of <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for advanced options for
--   the specified Elasticsearch domain.
advancedOptionsStatus_status :: Lens' AdvancedOptionsStatus OptionStatus
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.AdvancedOptionsStatus.AdvancedOptionsStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.AdvancedOptionsStatus.AdvancedOptionsStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.AdvancedOptionsStatus.AdvancedOptionsStatus

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode

pattern OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode_ACTIVE :: OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus

-- | Specifies the connection status of an outbound cross-cluster search
--   connection.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus</a> smart
--   constructor.
data OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus
OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode -> OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus

-- | Specifies verbose information for the outbound connection status.
[$sel:message:OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus'] :: OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The state code for outbound connection. This can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by destination domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by destination
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and cannot be used
--   further.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:statusCode:OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus'] :: OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus -> Maybe OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode

-- | Create a value of <a>OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus</a>
--   with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>outboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus_message</a> - Specifies
--   verbose information for the outbound connection status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCode:OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>outboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus_statusCode</a> - The
--   state code for outbound connection. This can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by destination domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by destination
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and cannot be used
--   further.</li>
--   </ul>
newOutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus :: OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus

-- | Specifies verbose information for the outbound connection status.
outboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus_message :: Lens' OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The state code for outbound connection. This can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by destination domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by destination
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and cannot be used
--   further.</li>
--   </ul>
outboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus_statusCode :: Lens' OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus (Maybe OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatusCode)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus.OutboundCrossClusterSearchConnectionStatus

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.PackageDetails

-- | Basic information about a package.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPackageDetails</a> smart constructor.
data PackageDetails
PackageDetails' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe PackageType -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe PackageStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ErrorDetails -> Maybe Text -> PackageDetails

-- | Internal ID of the package.
[$sel:packageID:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Currently supports only TXT-DICTIONARY.
[$sel:packageType:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe PackageType
[$sel:lastUpdatedAt:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Timestamp which tells creation date of the package.
[$sel:createdAt:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe POSIX

-- | User specified name of the package.
[$sel:packageName:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Current state of the package. Values are
--   COPYING/COPY_FAILED/AVAILABLE/DELETING/DELETE_FAILED
[$sel:packageStatus:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe PackageStatus

-- | User-specified description of the package.
[$sel:packageDescription:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null
--   otherwise.
[$sel:errorDetails:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe ErrorDetails
[$sel:availablePackageVersion:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>PackageDetails</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   TXT-DICTIONARY.
--

--   <a>packageDetails_lastUpdatedAt</a> - Undocumented member.

--   package.
--

--   <a>packageDetails_packageStatus</a> - Current state of the package.
--   Values are COPYING/COPY_FAILED/AVAILABLE/DELETING/DELETE_FAILED

--   <a>packageDetails_packageDescription</a> - User-specified description

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails

-- | Information on a package that is associated with a domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainPackageDetails</a> smart constructor.
data DomainPackageDetails
DomainPackageDetails' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe PackageType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe DomainPackageStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ErrorDetails -> Maybe Text -> DomainPackageDetails

-- | Timestamp of the most-recent update to the association status.
[$sel:lastUpdated:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Internal ID of the package.
[$sel:packageID:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Currently supports only TXT-DICTIONARY.
[$sel:packageType:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe PackageType

-- | User specified name of the package.
[$sel:packageName:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text
[$sel:packageVersion:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | State of the association. Values are
--   ASSOCIATING/ASSOCIATION_FAILED/ACTIVE/DISSOCIATING/DISSOCIATION_FAILED.
[$sel:domainPackageStatus:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe DomainPackageStatus

-- | Name of the domain you've associated a package with.
[$sel:domainName:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null
--   otherwise.
[$sel:errorDetails:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe ErrorDetails

-- | The relative path on Amazon ES nodes, which can be used as
--   synonym_path when the package is synonym file.
[$sel:referencePath:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainPackageDetails</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdated:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_lastUpdated</a> - Timestamp of the most-recent
--   update to the association status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageID:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageID</a> - Internal ID of the package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageType:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageType</a> - Currently supports only
--   TXT-DICTIONARY.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageName:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageName</a> - User specified name of the
--   package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageVersion:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageVersion</a> - Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainPackageStatus:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_domainPackageStatus</a> - State of the
--   association. Values are
--   ASSOCIATING/ASSOCIATION_FAILED/ACTIVE/DISSOCIATING/DISSOCIATION_FAILED.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainName:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_domainName</a> - Name of the domain you've
--   associated a package with.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorDetails:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_errorDetails</a> - Additional information if
--   the package is in an error state. Null otherwise.
--   
--   <a>$sel:referencePath:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_referencePath</a> - The relative path on
--   Amazon ES nodes, which can be used as synonym_path when the package is
--   synonym file.
newDomainPackageDetails :: DomainPackageDetails

-- | Timestamp of the most-recent update to the association status.
domainPackageDetails_lastUpdated :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Internal ID of the package.
domainPackageDetails_packageID :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | Currently supports only TXT-DICTIONARY.
domainPackageDetails_packageType :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe PackageType)

-- | User specified name of the package.
domainPackageDetails_packageName :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | Undocumented member.
domainPackageDetails_packageVersion :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | State of the association. Values are
--   ASSOCIATING/ASSOCIATION_FAILED/ACTIVE/DISSOCIATING/DISSOCIATION_FAILED.
domainPackageDetails_domainPackageStatus :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe DomainPackageStatus)

-- | Name of the domain you've associated a package with.
domainPackageDetails_domainName :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null
--   otherwise.
domainPackageDetails_errorDetails :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe ErrorDetails)

-- | The relative path on Amazon ES nodes, which can be used as
--   synonym_path when the package is synonym file.
domainPackageDetails_referencePath :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails

--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSAMLOptionsInput</a> smart constructor.
data SAMLOptionsInput
SAMLOptionsInput' :: Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe SAMLIdp -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> SAMLOptionsInput

-- | The SAML master username, which is stored in the Amazon Elasticsearch
--   Service domain's internal database.

-- | The backend role to which the SAML master user is mapped to.
[$sel:masterBackendRole:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe Text

-- | The duration, in minutes, after which a user session becomes inactive.
--   Acceptable values are between 1 and 1440, and the default value is 60.
[$sel:sessionTimeoutMinutes:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe Int

-- | The key to use for matching the SAML Subject attribute.
[$sel:subjectKey:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe Text

--   omitted.

--   <a>sAMLOptionsInput_masterBackendRole</a> - The backend role to which
--   the SAML master user is mapped to.
--

-- | Specifies Auto-Tune action type. Valid values are JVM_HEAP_SIZE_TUNING
--   and JVM_YOUNG_GEN_TUNING.
[$sel:actionType:ScheduledAutoTuneDetails'] :: ScheduledAutoTuneDetails -> Maybe ScheduledAutoTuneActionType

-- | Create a value of <a>ScheduledAutoTuneDetails</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--

--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:severity:ScheduledAutoTuneDetails'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledAutoTuneDetails_severity</a> - Specifies Auto-Tune action
--   severity. Valid values are LOW, MEDIUM and HIGH.
--   
--   <a>$sel:action:ScheduledAutoTuneDetails'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledAutoTuneDetails_action</a> - Specifies Auto-Tune action
--   description.
--   
--   <a>$sel:date:ScheduledAutoTuneDetails'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledAutoTuneDetails_date</a> - Specifies timestamp for the
--   Auto-Tune action scheduled for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:actionType:ScheduledAutoTuneDetails'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledAutoTuneDetails_actionType</a> - Specifies Auto-Tune
--   action type. Valid values are JVM_HEAP_SIZE_TUNING and
--   JVM_YOUNG_GEN_TUNING.
newScheduledAutoTuneDetails :: ScheduledAutoTuneDetails

-- | Specifies Auto-Tune action severity. Valid values are LOW, MEDIUM and
--   HIGH.
scheduledAutoTuneDetails_severity :: Lens' ScheduledAutoTuneDetails (Maybe ScheduledAutoTuneSeverityType)

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | The current options of an Elasticsearch domain service software
--   options.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newServiceSoftwareOptions</a> smart constructor.
data ServiceSoftwareOptions
ServiceSoftwareOptions' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe DeploymentStatus -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | Timestamp, in Epoch time, until which you can manually request a
--   service software update. After this date, we automatically update your
--   service software.
[$sel:automatedUpdateDate:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The current service software version that is present on the domain.
[$sel:currentVersion:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | <tt>True</tt> if a service software is never automatically updated.
--   <tt>False</tt> if a service software is automatically updated after
--   <tt>AutomatedUpdateDate</tt>.
[$sel:optionalDeployment:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | The status of your service software update. This field can take the
--   following values: <tt>ELIGIBLE</tt>, <tt>PENDING_UPDATE</tt>,
--   <tt>IN_PROGRESS</tt>, <tt>COMPLETED</tt>, and <tt>NOT_ELIGIBLE</tt>.
[$sel:updateStatus:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe DeploymentStatus

-- | <tt>True</tt> if you are able to cancel your service software version
--   update. <tt>False</tt> if you are not able to cancel your service
--   software version.
[$sel:cancellable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | <tt>True</tt> if you are able to update you service software version.
--   <tt>False</tt> if you are not able to update your service software
--   version.
[$sel:updateAvailable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | The description of the <tt>UpdateStatus</tt>.
[$sel:description:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | The new service software version if one is available.
[$sel:newVersion':ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ServiceSoftwareOptions</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:automatedUpdateDate:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_automatedUpdateDate</a> - Timestamp, in
--   Epoch time, until which you can manually request a service software
--   update. After this date, we automatically update your service
--   software.
--   
--   <a>$sel:currentVersion:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_currentVersion</a> - The current service
--   software version that is present on the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionalDeployment:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_optionalDeployment</a> - <tt>True</tt> if a
--   service software is never automatically updated. <tt>False</tt> if a
--   service software is automatically updated after
--   <tt>AutomatedUpdateDate</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateStatus:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_updateStatus</a> - The status of your
--   service software update. This field can take the following values:
--   <tt>ELIGIBLE</tt>, <tt>PENDING_UPDATE</tt>, <tt>IN_PROGRESS</tt>,
--   <tt>COMPLETED</tt>, and <tt>NOT_ELIGIBLE</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cancellable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_cancellable</a> - <tt>True</tt> if you are
--   able to cancel your service software version update. <tt>False</tt> if
--   you are not able to cancel your service software version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateAvailable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_updateAvailable</a> - <tt>True</tt> if you

--   <tt>UpdateStatus</tt>.

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Options to configure endpoint for the Elasticsearch domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainEndpointOptions</a> smart constructor.
data DomainEndpointOptions
DomainEndpointOptions' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe TLSSecurityPolicy -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Specify if only HTTPS endpoint should be enabled for the Elasticsearch
--   domain.
[$sel:enforceHTTPS:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specify the TLS security policy that needs to be applied to the HTTPS
--   endpoint of Elasticsearch domain. It can be one of the following
--   values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:tLSSecurityPolicy:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe TLSSecurityPolicy

-- | Specify if custom endpoint should be enabled for the Elasticsearch
--   domain.
[$sel:customEndpointEnabled:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specify the fully qualified domain for your custom endpoint.
[$sel:customEndpoint:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | Specify ACM certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
[$sel:customEndpointCertificateArn:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainEndpointOptions</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:enforceHTTPS:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_enforceHTTPS</a> - Specify if only HTTPS
--   endpoint should be enabled for the Elasticsearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tLSSecurityPolicy:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_tLSSecurityPolicy</a> - Specify the TLS
--   security policy that needs to be applied to the HTTPS endpoint of
--   Elasticsearch domain. It can be one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpointEnabled:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointEnabled</a> - Specify if custom
--   endpoint should be enabled for the Elasticsearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpoint:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpoint</a> - Specify the fully
--   qualified domain for your custom endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpointCertificateArn:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointCertificateArn</a> - Specify
--   ACM certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
newDomainEndpointOptions :: DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Specify if only HTTPS endpoint should be enabled for the Elasticsearch
--   domain.
domainEndpointOptions_enforceHTTPS :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specify the TLS security policy that needs to be applied to the HTTPS
--   endpoint of Elasticsearch domain. It can be one of the following
--   values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>
domainEndpointOptions_tLSSecurityPolicy :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe TLSSecurityPolicy)

-- | Specify if custom endpoint should be enabled for the Elasticsearch
--   domain.
domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointEnabled :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specify the fully qualified domain for your custom endpoint.
domainEndpointOptions_customEndpoint :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Text)

-- | Specify ACM certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointCertificateArn :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainEndpointOptions.DomainEndpointOptions
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainEndpointOptions.DomainEndpointOptions
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainEndpointOptions.DomainEndpointOptions
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.DomainEndpointOptions.DomainEndpointOptions

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag

-- | Specifies a key value pair for a resource tag.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTag</a> smart constructor.
data Tag
Tag' :: Text -> Text -> Tag

-- | Specifies the <tt>TagKey</tt>, the name of the tag. Tag keys must be
--   unique for the Elasticsearch domain to which they are attached.
[$sel:key:Tag'] :: Tag -> Text

-- | Specifies the <tt>TagValue</tt>, the value assigned to the
--   corresponding tag key. Tag values can be null and do not have to be
--   unique in a tag set. For example, you can have a key value pair in a
--   tag set of <tt>project : Trinity</tt> and <tt>cost-center :
--   Trinity</tt>
[$sel:value:Tag'] :: Tag -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Tag</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:key:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_key</a> - Specifies the <tt>TagKey</tt>,
--   the name of the tag. Tag keys must be unique for the Elasticsearch
--   domain to which they are attached.
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_value</a> - Specifies the
--   <tt>TagValue</tt>, the value assigned to the corresponding tag key.
--   Tag values can be null and do not have to be unique in a tag set. For
--   example, you can have a key value pair in a tag set of <tt>project :
--   Trinity</tt> and <tt>cost-center : Trinity</tt>
newTag :: Text -> Text -> Tag

-- | Specifies the <tt>TagKey</tt>, the name of the tag. Tag keys must be
--   unique for the Elasticsearch domain to which they are attached.
tag_key :: Lens' Tag Text

-- | Specifies the <tt>TagValue</tt>, the value assigned to the
--   corresponding tag key. Tag values can be null and do not have to be
--   unique in a tag set. For example, you can have a key value pair in a
--   tag set of <tt>project : Trinity</tt> and <tt>cost-center :
--   Trinity</tt>
tag_value :: Lens' Tag Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag.Tag
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag.Tag
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag.Tag
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag.Tag
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.Tag.Tag

--   of a maintenance schedule duration. Valid value is HOURS. See the
--   <a>Developer Guide</a> for more information.

--   the <a>Developer Guide</a> for more information.

--   HOURS. See the <a>Developer Guide</a> for more information.

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.AutoTuneOptions

--   domain, rollback state when disabling Auto-Tune options and list of
--   maintenance schedules.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAutoTuneOptions</a> smart constructor.
data AutoTuneOptions

--   DISABLED.
[$sel:desiredState:AutoTuneOptions'] :: AutoTuneOptions -> Maybe AutoTuneDesiredState

--   Valid values are NO_ROLLBACK, DEFAULT_ROLLBACK.
[$sel:rollbackOnDisable:AutoTuneOptions'] :: AutoTuneOptions -> Maybe RollbackOnDisable

-- | Specifies list of maitenance schedules. See the <a>Developer Guide</a>
--   for more information.
[$sel:maintenanceSchedules:AutoTuneOptions'] :: AutoTuneOptions -> Maybe [AutoTuneMaintenanceSchedule]

--   omitted.

--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   <a>$sel:desiredState:AutoTuneOptions'</a>,
--   <a>autoTuneOptions_desiredState</a> - Specifies the Auto-Tune desired
--   state. Valid values are ENABLED, DISABLED.
--   
--   <a>$sel:rollbackOnDisable:AutoTuneOptions'</a>,
--   <a>autoTuneOptions_rollbackOnDisable</a> - Specifies the rollback
--   state while disabling Auto-Tune for the domain. Valid values are
--   NO_ROLLBACK, DEFAULT_ROLLBACK.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maintenanceSchedules:AutoTuneOptions'</a>,
--   <a>autoTuneOptions_maintenanceSchedules</a> - Specifies list of
--   maitenance schedules. See the <a>Developer Guide</a> for more
--   information.

--   DISABLED.

--   Valid values are NO_ROLLBACK, DEFAULT_ROLLBACK.

--   for more information.

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.AutoTuneOptionsStatus

-- | Specifies the status of Auto-Tune options for the specified
--   Elasticsearch domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAutoTuneOptionsStatus</a> smart constructor.
data AutoTuneOptionsStatus

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem

-- | Represents a single step of the Upgrade or Upgrade Eligibility Check
--   workflow.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeStepItem</a> smart constructor.
data UpgradeStepItem
UpgradeStepItem' :: Maybe UpgradeStatus -> Maybe Double -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe UpgradeStep -> UpgradeStepItem

-- | The status of a particular step during an upgrade. The status can take
--   one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:upgradeStepStatus:UpgradeStepItem'] :: UpgradeStepItem -> Maybe UpgradeStatus

-- | The Floating point value representing progress percentage of a
--   particular step.
[$sel:progressPercent:UpgradeStepItem'] :: UpgradeStepItem -> Maybe Double

-- | A list of strings containing detailed information about the errors
--   encountered in a particular step.
[$sel:issues:UpgradeStepItem'] :: UpgradeStepItem -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Represents one of 3 steps that an Upgrade or Upgrade Eligibility Check
--   does through:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PreUpgradeCheck</li>
--   <li>Snapshot</li>
--   <li>Upgrade</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:upgradeStep:UpgradeStepItem'] :: UpgradeStepItem -> Maybe UpgradeStep

-- | Create a value of <a>UpgradeStepItem</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeStepStatus:UpgradeStepItem'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeStepItem_upgradeStepStatus</a> - The status of a particular
--   step during an upgrade. The status can take one of the following
--   values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:progressPercent:UpgradeStepItem'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeStepItem_progressPercent</a> - The Floating point value
--   representing progress percentage of a particular step.
--   
--   <a>$sel:issues:UpgradeStepItem'</a>, <a>upgradeStepItem_issues</a> - A
--   list of strings containing detailed information about the errors
--   encountered in a particular step.
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeStep:UpgradeStepItem'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeStepItem_upgradeStep</a> - Represents one of 3 steps that an
--   Upgrade or Upgrade Eligibility Check does through:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PreUpgradeCheck</li>
--   <li>Snapshot</li>
--   <li>Upgrade</li>
--   </ul>
newUpgradeStepItem :: UpgradeStepItem

-- | The status of a particular step during an upgrade. The status can take
--   one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
upgradeStepItem_upgradeStepStatus :: Lens' UpgradeStepItem (Maybe UpgradeStatus)

-- | The Floating point value representing progress percentage of a
--   particular step.
upgradeStepItem_progressPercent :: Lens' UpgradeStepItem (Maybe Double)

-- | A list of strings containing detailed information about the errors
--   encountered in a particular step.
upgradeStepItem_issues :: Lens' UpgradeStepItem (Maybe [Text])

-- | Represents one of 3 steps that an Upgrade or Upgrade Eligibility Check
--   does through:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PreUpgradeCheck</li>
--   <li>Snapshot</li>
--   <li>Upgrade</li>
--   </ul>
upgradeStepItem_upgradeStep :: Lens' UpgradeStepItem (Maybe UpgradeStep)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem


module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory

-- | History of the last 10 Upgrades and Upgrade Eligibility Checks.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeHistory</a> smart constructor.
data UpgradeHistory
UpgradeHistory' :: Maybe UpgradeStatus -> Maybe [UpgradeStepItem] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> UpgradeHistory

-- | The overall status of the update. The status can take one of the
--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:upgradeStatus:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe UpgradeStatus

-- | A list of <tt> UpgradeStepItem </tt> s representing information about
--   each step performed as pard of a specific Upgrade or Upgrade
--   Eligibility Check.
[$sel:stepsList:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe [UpgradeStepItem]

-- | A string that describes the update briefly
[$sel:upgradeName:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe Text

-- | UTC Timestamp at which the Upgrade API call was made in
--   "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
[$sel:startTimestamp:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Create a value of <a>UpgradeHistory</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeStatus:UpgradeHistory'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeHistory_upgradeStatus</a> - The overall status of the
--   update. The status can take one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:stepsList:UpgradeHistory'</a>, <a>upgradeHistory_stepsList</a>
--   - A list of <tt> UpgradeStepItem </tt> s representing information
--   about each step performed as pard of a specific Upgrade or Upgrade
--   Eligibility Check.
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeName:UpgradeHistory'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeHistory_upgradeName</a> - A string that describes the update
--   briefly
--   
--   <a>$sel:startTimestamp:UpgradeHistory'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeHistory_startTimestamp</a> - UTC Timestamp at which the
--   Upgrade API call was made in "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
newUpgradeHistory :: UpgradeHistory

-- | The overall status of the update. The status can take one of the
--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
upgradeHistory_upgradeStatus :: Lens' UpgradeHistory (Maybe UpgradeStatus)

-- | A list of <tt> UpgradeStepItem </tt> s representing information about
--   each step performed as pard of a specific Upgrade or Upgrade
--   Eligibility Check.
upgradeHistory_stepsList :: Lens' UpgradeHistory (Maybe [UpgradeStepItem])

-- | A string that describes the update briefly
upgradeHistory_upgradeName :: Lens' UpgradeHistory (Maybe Text)

-- | UTC Timestamp at which the Upgrade API call was made in
--   "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
upgradeHistory_startTimestamp :: Lens' UpgradeHistory (Maybe UTCTime)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory

--   the domain was created with VPCOptions.

--   for VPC endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:subnetIds:VPCDerivedInfo'</a>, <a>vPCDerivedInfo_subnetIds</a>
--   - Specifies the subnets for VPC endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vPCId:VPCDerivedInfo'</a>, <a>vPCDerivedInfo_vPCId</a> - The

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.EBSOptions

-- | Options to enable, disable, and specify the properties of EBS storage
--   volumes. For more information, see <a>Configuring EBS-based
--   Storage</a>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEBSOptions</a> smart constructor.
data EBSOptions
EBSOptions' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe VolumeType -> Maybe Bool -> EBSOptions

-- | Integer to specify the size of an EBS volume.
[$sel:volumeSize:EBSOptions'] :: EBSOptions -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the IOPD for a Provisioned IOPS EBS volume (SSD).
[$sel:iops:EBSOptions'] :: EBSOptions -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the volume type for EBS-based storage.
[$sel:volumeType:EBSOptions'] :: EBSOptions -> Maybe VolumeType

-- | Specifies whether EBS-based storage is enabled.
[$sel:eBSEnabled:EBSOptions'] :: EBSOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>EBSOptions</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:volumeSize:EBSOptions'</a>, <a>eBSOptions_volumeSize</a> -
--   Integer to specify the size of an EBS volume.
--   
--   <a>$sel:iops:EBSOptions'</a>, <a>eBSOptions_iops</a> - Specifies the
--   IOPD for a Provisioned IOPS EBS volume (SSD).
--   
--   <a>$sel:volumeType:EBSOptions'</a>, <a>eBSOptions_volumeType</a> -
--   Specifies the volume type for EBS-based storage.
--   
--   <a>$sel:eBSEnabled:EBSOptions'</a>, <a>eBSOptions_eBSEnabled</a> -
--   Specifies whether EBS-based storage is enabled.
newEBSOptions :: EBSOptions

-- | Integer to specify the size of an EBS volume.
eBSOptions_volumeSize :: Lens' EBSOptions (Maybe Int)

-- | Specifies the IOPD for a Provisioned IOPS EBS volume (SSD).
eBSOptions_iops :: Lens' EBSOptions (Maybe Int)

-- | Specifies the volume type for EBS-based storage.
eBSOptions_volumeType :: Lens' EBSOptions (Maybe VolumeType)

-- | Specifies whether EBS-based storage is enabled.
eBSOptions_eBSEnabled :: Lens' EBSOptions (Maybe Bool)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.EBSOptions.EBSOptions
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.EBSOptions.EBSOptions
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.EBSOptions.EBSOptions

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.ElasticsearchClusterConfig

-- | Specifies the configuration for the domain cluster, such as the type
--   and number of instances.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newElasticsearchClusterConfig</a> smart constructor.
data ElasticsearchClusterConfig
ElasticsearchClusterConfig' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe ESPartitionInstanceType -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ColdStorageOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe ESPartitionInstanceType -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe ZoneAwarenessConfig -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ESWarmPartitionInstanceType -> ElasticsearchClusterConfig

-- | Total number of dedicated master nodes, active and on standby, for the
--   cluster.
[$sel:dedicatedMasterCount:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | The instance type for a dedicated master node.
[$sel:dedicatedMasterType:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe ESPartitionInstanceType

-- | A boolean value to indicate whether a dedicated master node is
--   enabled. See <a>About Dedicated Master Nodes</a> for more information.
[$sel:dedicatedMasterEnabled:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe Bool

-- | The number of instances in the specified domain cluster.
[$sel:instanceCount:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the <tt>ColdStorageOptions</tt> config for Elasticsearch
--   Domain
[$sel:coldStorageOptions:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe ColdStorageOptions

-- | A boolean value to indicate whether zone awareness is enabled. See
--   <a>About Zone Awareness</a> for more information.
[$sel:zoneAwarenessEnabled:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe Bool

-- | The instance type for an Elasticsearch cluster. UltraWarm instance
--   types are not supported for data instances.
[$sel:instanceType:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe ESPartitionInstanceType

-- | True to enable warm storage.
[$sel:warmEnabled:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the zone awareness configuration for a domain when zone
--   awareness is enabled.
[$sel:zoneAwarenessConfig:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe ZoneAwarenessConfig

-- | The number of warm nodes in the cluster.
[$sel:warmCount:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | The instance type for the Elasticsearch cluster's warm nodes.
[$sel:warmType:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'] :: ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> Maybe ESWarmPartitionInstanceType

-- | Create a value of <a>ElasticsearchClusterConfig</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding

--   <a>$sel:dedicatedMasterType:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'</a>,

--   
--   <a>$sel:dedicatedMasterEnabled:ElasticsearchClusterConfig'</a>,

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.ElasticsearchDomainStatus

-- | The current status of an Elasticsearch domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newElasticsearchDomainStatus</a> smart constructor.
data ElasticsearchDomainStatus
ElasticsearchDomainStatus' :: Maybe EBSOptions -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsOutput -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption) -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe SnapshotOptions -> Maybe CognitoOptions -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe VPCDerivedInfo -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Maybe Text -> Text -> Text -> Text -> ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> ElasticsearchDomainStatus

-- | The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the specified domain. See <a>Configuring
--   EBS-based Storage</a> for more information.
[$sel:eBSOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe EBSOptions

-- | Specifies the status of the <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt>.
[$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
[$sel:accessPolicies:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The current status of the Elasticsearch domain's service software.
[$sel:serviceSoftwareOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | The current status of the Elasticsearch domain's Auto-Tune options.
[$sel:autoTuneOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsOutput

-- | Log publishing options for the given domain.
[$sel:logPublishingOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption)

-- | The current status of the Elasticsearch domain's advanced security
--   options.
[$sel:advancedSecurityOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptions

-- | The domain creation status. <tt>True</tt> if the creation of an
--   Elasticsearch domain is complete. <tt>False</tt> if domain creation is
--   still in progress.
[$sel:created:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the status of the <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt>
[$sel:snapshotOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe SnapshotOptions

-- | The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Amazon Cognito Authentication for Kibana</a>.
[$sel:cognitoOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe CognitoOptions

-- | Specifies the status of the <tt>EncryptionAtRestOptions</tt>.
[$sel:encryptionAtRestOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions

-- | The domain deletion status. <tt>True</tt> if a delete request has been
--   received for the domain but resource cleanup is still in progress.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the domain has not been deleted. Once domain
--   deletion is complete, the status of the domain is no longer returned.
[$sel:deleted:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>VPC Endpoints for Amazon Elasticsearch Service
--   Domains</a>.
[$sel:vPCOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe VPCDerivedInfo

-- | Map containing the Elasticsearch domain endpoints used to submit index
--   and search requests. Example <tt>key, value</tt>:
--   <tt>'vpc','vpc-endpoint-h2dsd34efgyghrtguk5gt6j2foh4.us-east-1.es.amazonaws.com'</tt>.
[$sel:endpoints:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)

-- | The current status of the Elasticsearch domain's endpoint options.
[$sel:domainEndpointOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions

-- | The status of the Elasticsearch domain configuration. <tt>True</tt> if
--   Amazon Elasticsearch Service is processing configuration changes.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the configuration is active.
[$sel:processing:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Elasticsearch domain endpoint that you use to submit index and
--   search requests.
[$sel:endpoint:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of an Elasticsearch domain version upgrade. <tt>True</tt>
--   if Amazon Elasticsearch Service is undergoing a version upgrade.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the configuration is active.
[$sel:upgradeProcessing:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the status of the <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt>
[$sel:advancedOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)
[$sel:elasticsearchVersion:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The unique identifier for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
[$sel:domainId:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Text

-- | The name of an Elasticsearch domain. Domain names are unique across
--   the domains owned by an account within an AWS region. Domain names
--   start with a letter or number and can contain the following
--   characters: a-z (lowercase), 0-9, and - (hyphen).
[$sel:domainName:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Text

-- | The Amazon resource name (ARN) of an Elasticsearch domain. See
--   <a>Identifiers for IAM Entities</a> in <i>Using AWS Identity and
--   Access Management</i> for more information.
[$sel:arn:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> Text

-- | The type and number of instances in the domain cluster.
[$sel:elasticsearchClusterConfig:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'] :: ElasticsearchDomainStatus -> ElasticsearchClusterConfig

-- | Create a value of <a>ElasticsearchDomainStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:eBSOptions:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'</a>,

--   more information.

--   
--   <a>$sel:elasticsearchClusterConfig:ElasticsearchDomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>elasticsearchDomainStatus_elasticsearchClusterConfig</a> - The type
--   and number of instances in the domain cluster.
newElasticsearchDomainStatus :: Text -> Text -> Text -> ElasticsearchClusterConfig -> ElasticsearchDomainStatus

-- | The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the specified domain. See <a>Configuring
--   EBS-based Storage</a> for more information.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_eBSOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe EBSOptions)

-- | Specifies the status of the <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt>.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions)

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_accessPolicies :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The current status of the Elasticsearch domain's service software.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_serviceSoftwareOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe ServiceSoftwareOptions)

-- | The current status of the Elasticsearch domain's Auto-Tune options.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_autoTuneOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe AutoTuneOptionsOutput)

-- | Log publishing options for the given domain.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_logPublishingOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption))

-- | The current status of the Elasticsearch domain's advanced security
--   options.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_advancedSecurityOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptions)

-- | The domain creation status. <tt>True</tt> if the creation of an
--   Elasticsearch domain is complete. <tt>False</tt> if domain creation is
--   still in progress.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_created :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the status of the <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt>
elasticsearchDomainStatus_snapshotOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe SnapshotOptions)

-- | The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Amazon Cognito Authentication for Kibana</a>.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_cognitoOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe CognitoOptions)

-- | Specifies the status of the <tt>EncryptionAtRestOptions</tt>.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_encryptionAtRestOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions)

-- | The domain deletion status. <tt>True</tt> if a delete request has been
--   received for the domain but resource cleanup is still in progress.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the domain has not been deleted. Once domain
--   deletion is complete, the status of the domain is no longer returned.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_deleted :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe Bool)

-- | The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>VPC Endpoints for Amazon Elasticsearch Service
--   Domains</a>.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_vPCOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe VPCDerivedInfo)

-- | Map containing the Elasticsearch domain endpoints used to submit index
--   and search requests. Example <tt>key, value</tt>:
--   <tt>'vpc','vpc-endpoint-h2dsd34efgyghrtguk5gt6j2foh4.us-east-1.es.amazonaws.com'</tt>.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_endpoints :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe (HashMap Text Text))

-- | The current status of the Elasticsearch domain's endpoint options.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_domainEndpointOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe DomainEndpointOptions)

-- | The status of the Elasticsearch domain configuration. <tt>True</tt> if
--   Amazon Elasticsearch Service is processing configuration changes.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the configuration is active.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_processing :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe Bool)

-- | The Elasticsearch domain endpoint that you use to submit index and
--   search requests.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_endpoint :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The status of an Elasticsearch domain version upgrade. <tt>True</tt>
--   if Amazon Elasticsearch Service is undergoing a version upgrade.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the configuration is active.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_upgradeProcessing :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the status of the <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt>
elasticsearchDomainStatus_advancedOptions :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe (HashMap Text Text))

-- | Undocumented member.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_elasticsearchVersion :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The unique identifier for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_domainId :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus Text

-- | The name of an Elasticsearch domain. Domain names are unique across
--   the domains owned by an account within an AWS region. Domain names
--   start with a letter or number and can contain the following
--   characters: a-z (lowercase), 0-9, and - (hyphen).
elasticsearchDomainStatus_domainName :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus Text

-- | The Amazon resource name (ARN) of an Elasticsearch domain. See
--   <a>Identifiers for IAM Entities</a> in <i>Using AWS Identity and
--   Access Management</i> for more information.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_arn :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus Text

-- | The type and number of instances in the domain cluster.
elasticsearchDomainStatus_elasticsearchClusterConfig :: Lens' ElasticsearchDomainStatus ElasticsearchClusterConfig
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.ElasticsearchDomainStatus.ElasticsearchDomainStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.ElasticsearchDomainStatus.ElasticsearchDomainStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.ElasticsearchDomainStatus.ElasticsearchDomainStatus
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types.ElasticsearchDomainStatus.ElasticsearchDomainStatus

module Network.AWS.ElasticSearch.Types

-- | API version <tt>2015-01-01</tt> of the Amazon Elasticsearch Service
--   SDK configuration.
defaultService :: Service

-- | An exception for missing / invalid input fields. Gives http status
--   code of 400.
_ValidationException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occurred because user does not have permissions to access the
--   resource. Returns HTTP status code 403.
_AccessDeniedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An exception for creating a resource that already exists. Gives http
--   status code of 400.
_ResourceAlreadyExistsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occurred because the client attempts to remove a resource
--   that is currently in use. Returns HTTP status code 409.
_ConflictException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occurred while processing the request.
_BaseException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occured because the client wanted to access a not supported
--   operation. Gives http status code of 409.
_DisabledOperationException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The request processing has failed because of an unknown error,
--   exception or failure (the failure is internal to the service) . Gives
--   http status code of 500.
_InternalException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An exception for trying to create or access sub-resource that is
--   either invalid or not supported. Gives http status code of 409.
_InvalidTypeException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An exception for accessing or deleting a resource that does not exist.
--   Gives http status code of 400.
_ResourceNotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The request processing has failed because of invalid pagination token
--   provided by customer. Returns an HTTP status code of 400.
_InvalidPaginationTokenException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An exception for trying to create more than allowed resources or
--   sub-resources. Gives http status code of 409.
_LimitExceededException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Specifies the Auto-Tune desired state. Valid values are ENABLED,
--   DISABLED.
newtype AutoTuneDesiredState
AutoTuneDesiredState' :: Text -> AutoTuneDesiredState

pattern AutoTuneDesiredState_ENABLED :: AutoTuneDesiredState

--   states see the <a>Developer Guide</a>.

pattern AutoTuneState_ENABLED :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_ENABLE_IN_PROGRESS :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_ERROR :: AutoTuneState

-- | Type of Log File, it can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>INDEX_SLOW_LOGS: Index slow logs contain insert requests that took
--   more time than configured index query log threshold to execute.</li>
--   <li>SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS: Search slow logs contain search queries that
--   took more time than configured search query log threshold to
--   execute.</li>
--   <li>ES_APPLICATION_LOGS: Elasticsearch application logs contain
--   information about errors and warnings raised during the operation of
--   the service and can be useful for troubleshooting.</li>
--   <li>AUDIT_LOGS: Audit logs contain records of user requests for access
--   from the domain.</li>
--   </ul>
newtype LogType
LogType' :: Text -> LogType
[fromLogType] :: LogType -> Text
pattern LogType_AUDIT_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_ES_APPLICATION_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_INDEX_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType

-- | The state of a requested change. One of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Processing: The request change is still in-process.</li>
--   <li>Active: The request change is processed and deployed to the
--   Elasticsearch domain.</li>
--   </ul>
newtype OptionState

[fromOptionState] :: OptionState -> Text
pattern OptionState_Active :: OptionState
pattern OptionState_Processing :: OptionState
pattern OptionState_RequiresIndexDocuments :: OptionState

-- | List of limits that are specific to a given InstanceType and for each

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAdditionalLimit</a> smart constructor.
data AdditionalLimit

--   each of it's <tt> InstanceRole </tt> etc. Attributes and their
--   details:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>MaximumNumberOfDataNodesSupported</li>
--   <li>MaximumNumberOfDataNodesWithoutMasterNode</li>
--   </ul>

-- | Status of the advanced options for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
--   Currently, the following advanced options are available:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Option to allow references to indices in an HTTP request body.
--   Must be <tt>false</tt> when configuring access to individual
--   sub-resources. By default, the value is <tt>true</tt>. See
--   <a>Configuration Advanced Options</a> for more information.</li>
--   <li>Option to specify the percentage of heap space that is allocated
--   to field data. By default, this setting is unbounded.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Configuring Advanced Options</a>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAdvancedOptionsStatus</a> smart constructor.
data AdvancedOptionsStatus
AdvancedOptionsStatus' :: HashMap Text Text -> OptionStatus -> AdvancedOptionsStatus

--   Elasticsearch domain.
[$sel:options:AdvancedOptionsStatus'] :: AdvancedOptionsStatus -> HashMap Text Text

-- | Specifies the status of <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for advanced options for
--   the specified Elasticsearch domain.
[$sel:status:AdvancedOptionsStatus'] :: AdvancedOptionsStatus -> OptionStatus

-- | Create a value of <a>AdvancedOptionsStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:options:AdvancedOptionsStatus'</a>,
--   <a>advancedOptionsStatus_options</a> - Specifies the status of
--   advanced options for the specified Elasticsearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:AdvancedOptionsStatus'</a>,
--   <a>advancedOptionsStatus_status</a> - Specifies the status of
--   <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for advanced options for the specified
--   Elasticsearch domain.
newAdvancedOptionsStatus :: OptionStatus -> AdvancedOptionsStatus

-- | Specifies the status of advanced options for the specified
--   Elasticsearch domain.
advancedOptionsStatus_options :: Lens' AdvancedOptionsStatus (HashMap Text Text)

-- | Specifies the status of <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for advanced options for
--   the specified Elasticsearch domain.
advancedOptionsStatus_status :: Lens' AdvancedOptionsStatus OptionStatus

--   maintenance schedules.

--   DISABLED.
